Kinyuru Munuhe @kinyurumunuhe Directorate of Criminal Investigations director George Kinoti has effected far-reaching changes involving 368 officers between the ranks of constables and chief inspectors. Ninety-seven officers are in the ranks of Chief Inspectors and Inspectors of Police while 271 others are in the ranks of police constables, corporals, eight sergeants and one senior sergeant of police. “The officers should report to their new stations by March 6, 2018.” A circular signed by director of Personnel Mary Kaol on behalf of Kinoti read in part. Those affected are involved in primary operational duties and investigations right from the station where cases are made water tight with preservation of evidence or diluted.